defaultThe UK currently enjoys a high degree of food securitydefault in terms of access,
default availability, resilience and variety of food supply.  This is built on both a strong food production base in the UK and access to a wide variety of markets through the EU and an open, rules-based world trading system. 
defaultUK food security is supported by cons
defaultumer prosperity and income, which is addressed through the Government’s focus on growth
