default&#xa0; 
defaultWhile there are a number of working definitions of food security, the common elements of these definitions are the availability, access, affordability, safety and resilience of food. T
defaulthe 
default20
default10 
defaultUK Food Security Assessment
default 
defaultanalysed the UK’s food security position across six themes relating to these elements – global availability, global resource sustainability, UK availability of access, UK food chain resilience, household food security, and sa
defaultfety and confidence.
default9.
default&#xa0; 
defaultEach theme consists of a headline indicator, which captures a major or representative element of the theme, and several supporting indicators which explore related aspects of the theme. 
defaultIn 2012, an 
defaultinternal analysis 
defaultof these indicators
default 
defaultconcluded that the 2010 Assessment remained valid in the medium term but would be updated at 6-8 year intervals if warranted. This reflects the fact that many of the indicators in the assessment are relatively slow-moving or reflect structural issues whic
defaulth do not tend to see significant changes over a short period of time.  However, some indicators have 
defaultchanged
