defaultThe UK food chain 
defaultis competitive relative to many other European countries. According to Eurostat, food prices in Germany are 2% more expensive than the UK. In France
default,
default they are 5% more expensive, and in Ireland 13% - UK consumers are benefiting from our competitive market. 
default34.
default&#xa0; 
defaultHowever, in a competitive market there is less slack when underlying prices do rise. So when there are changes in the fundamental drivers of food price inflation (commodity prices, exchange rate, oil prices), consumer prices will adjust to those underlyin
defaultg changes. Whilst 
defaultour 
defaultfood prices have risen faster than our neighbours, the 
defaultaverage
default 
defaultprice of food remains lower.
