defaultntensification of agriculture, producing more with less input and impact. Government is investing £160m in translational research led and co-funded by industry to strengthen links between science and technology to drive innovation and its uptake into farmi
defaultng to improve the efficiency, cost effectiveness, and productivity in agriculture; increase access and uptake of knowledge transfer; and promote better access to international markets and export opportunities. 
default56.
default&#xa0; 
defaultWe are also working with the Technology Strat
defaultegy Board 
default(TSB) 
defaultto drive innovation to support a more competitive, resilient and sustainable agri-food sector via the £90m
